-- Mediaset, Fondiaria-Sai, Monte Paschi May Be Active: Italy Equity Preview
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2010-11-11T05:00:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/mediaset-fondiaria-sai-monte-paschi-may-be-active-italy-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  The benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  declined 520.47, or 2.4
percent, to 21,058.01 in Milan.  Mediaset SpA (MS IM): The broadcaster controlled by Italian
Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi, fell the most in more than 17
months in Milan trading after reporting a bigger-than-expected
net loss in the third quarter. Mediaset declined 6.5 percent to
5.06 euros.  Fondiaria-Sai SpA  (FSA IM): A capital increase of Italy’s
second-largest insurer is possible, though “improbable,” Chief
Executive Officer Fausto Marchionni said in a conference call.
The company posted its fifth consecutive quarterly loss.
Fondiaria shares fell 3.9 percent to 7.05 euros.  Monte dei Paschi di Siena SpA  (BMPS IM): Italy’s third-
biggest bank is scheduled to release third-quarter results. The
shares dropped 2.2 percent to 92 euro cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
